CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, April 10, 1954, page 21, reads: "Keynote Speaker - Mal Goode, Pittsburgh Courier and WHOD news commentator, and the leading figure in the case against alleged police brutality, keynoted the mass meeting."
TitMainTitle: Mal Goode, standing at podium with two microphones, giving the keynote address at a police brutality meeting at Bethel AME Church on Webster Avenue in the Hill District
